  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas had mixed feelings about \"The Force Awakens.\" In various interviews, he expressed that while he thought the film was well-made, he felt that it was too nostalgic and didn't offer anything new. Lucas commented that Disney, which acquired Lucasfilm, opted to make a movie that would appeal to fans by revisiting familiar themes and elements from the original trilogy, rather than taking risks and exploring new directions for the saga. He mentioned that he had his own ideas for the sequel trilogy that were not used, which added to his disappointment.",
